# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:7
translate french counselorconversation5_0c2aa4f4:

    # pc "I kind of miss Brazil."
    pc "Le Brésil me manque un peu."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:8
translate french counselorconversation5_2ec566c7:

    # sc "I bet. Was it nice there?"
    sc "Je m'en doute. C'était sympa là-bas ?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:9
translate french counselorconversation5_ef088408:

    # pc "It was, most of the time."
    pc "Oui, la plupart du temps."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:10
translate french counselorconversation5_ffefa487:

    # sc "Most of the time?"
    sc "La plupart du temps ?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:11
translate french counselorconversation5_f6155a33:

    # pc "Well the places that I stayed at were very nice."
    pc "Eh bien, les endroits où j'ai séjourné étaient très agréables."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:12
translate french counselorconversation5_444ece6f:

    # pc "But Brazil has a sort of split-personality."
    pc "Mais le Brésil a en quelque sorte une double personnalité."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:13
translate french counselorconversation5_9247b82f:

    # pc "It's absolutely beautiful in most of the places that I stayed."
    pc "C'est absolument magnifique dans la plupart des endroits où j'ai séjourné."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:14
translate french counselorconversation5_6ce76dfd:

    # pc "But occasionally, I saw the other side, where people were so poor and hungry and had no way to better themselves."
    pc "Mais parfois, j’ai vu l’autre facette, où les gens étaient si pauvres et affamés et n’avaient aucun moyen de s’en sortir."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:15
translate french counselorconversation5_64352ea1:

    # sc "That must have been eye-opening."
    sc "Ça a dû t’ouvrir les yeux."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:16
translate french counselorconversation5_ad0a9fab:

    # pc "It was. I know that people are like that in places,"
    pc "Oui. Je sais que les gens sont comme ça dans certains endroits,"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:17
translate french counselorconversation5_b47c5612:

    # pc "But it was so strange to see all of that, then go back to the dorm where I was living and nobody seemed to care."
    pc "Mais c’était tellement étrange de voir tout ça, puis de retourner à la résidence où je vivais et où personne ne semblait s’en soucier."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:18
translate french counselorconversation5_ba9df9c6:

    # sc "We tend to ignore the nasty things in life that don't affect us personally."
    sc "On a tendance à ignorer les aspects déplaisants de la vie qui ne nous touchent pas personnellement."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:19
translate french counselorconversation5_34e34dc1:

    # sc "It's a sort of coping mechanism. If we were constantly worried about every bad thing happening, we'd probably have a stroke."
    sc "C'est une sorte de mécanisme de défense. Si on s'inquiétait constamment de toutes les mauvaises choses qui arrivent, on ferait probablement un AVC."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:20
translate french counselorconversation5_e46768d7:

    # pc "I guess so, it's just hard to put some of that stuff out of my mind."
    pc "Je suppose, mais c'est juste difficile de chasser certaines de ces choses de mon esprit."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:21
translate french counselorconversation5_2426cfe6:

    # sc "You shouldn't. You should keep it there. It will make you a better person."
    sc "Tu ne devrais pas. Tu devrais les garder en tête. Ça fera de toi une meilleure personne."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:22
translate french counselorconversation5_4a449be8:

    # sc "Know that these things are happening, and know that you are privileged to have the life that you have."
    sc "Sache que ces choses se produisent, et sache que tu as la chance d'avoir la vie que tu as."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:23
translate french counselorconversation5_e88d7ffc:

    # pc "You're right."
    pc "Tu as raison."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:25
translate french counselorconversation5_067380d2:

    # sc "You have a good heart. Have you seen The Breakfast Club?"
    sc "Tu as bon cœur. Tu as vu The Breakfast Club ?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:28
translate french counselorconversation5_a6773fcb:

    # pc "Sure. Everybody has seen that, right?"
    pc "Bien sûr. Tout le monde l’a vu, non ?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:30
translate french counselorconversation5_8c93b784:

    # pc "I haven't seen it."
    pc "Je ne l’ai pas vu."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:31
translate french counselorconversation5_14e2d7b8:

    # sc "Well there's a line in it that Ally Sheedy says."
    sc "Eh bien, il y a une réplique qu’Ally Sheedy dit dans ce film."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:32
translate french counselorconversation5_314554fe:

    # sc "She says, \"When you grow up, your heart dies.\""
    sc "Elle dit : « Quand on grandit, notre cœur meurt. »"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:33
translate french counselorconversation5_67060d07:

    # sc "And it's true for a lot of people. As they grow up, they become jaded and cynical and stop caring about things."
    sc "Et c’est vrai pour beaucoup de gens. En grandissant, ils deviennent blasés et cyniques et cessent de se soucier des choses."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:34
translate french counselorconversation5_9123a037:

    # sc "But you're still young. You have a good heart. Don't let it die, okay?"
    sc "Mais tu es encore jeune. Tu as bon cœur. Ne le laisse pas mourir, d’accord ?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:35
translate french counselorconversation5_dd9a629d:

    # pc "I won't."
    pc "Je ne le laisserai pas mourir."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:37
translate french counselorconversation5_37653c95:

    # sc "Okay, well you better get to class."
    sc "Bon, tu ferais mieux d’aller en cours."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:38
translate french counselorconversation5_a8c43555:

    # pc "Okay, I'll see you next time Gertrude."
    pc "D’accord, à la prochaine, Gertrude."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:39
translate french counselorconversation5_1b784c07:

    # sc "Bye, [pcname]."
    sc "Au revoir, [pcname]."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:40
translate french counselorconversation5_e4b88e88:

    # "With that, I stand up and head to class."
    "Sur ce, je me lève et me dirige vers la salle de classe."

